results.name: a(n) is the least k such that A122953(k) = n.
comment: All positive terms of A112510 belong to this sequence.
The first known odd terms are a(1) = 1, a(5) = 11 and a(77) = 61321.
The sequence is not strictly increasing; for example a(17) = 186 and a(18) = 184.
The binary plot of the first terms has interesting features (see Links section).
link: Rémy Sigrist, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..288

example: The first occurrence of 6 in A122953 is A122953(12) = 6, hence a(6) = 12.
